 Illinois Zeta  Illinois Zeta UIC College of Engineering UIC College of Engineering Home Contact Us Our History Calendar Updates Service Hours Log Hours Information Initiate Information Home Our History  Edward Higginson Williams  Jr The Tau Beta Pi Association  national engineering honor society was founded at Lehigh University in      by Dr  Edward Higginson Williams  Jr  or by their attainments as alumni in the field of engineering  and to foster a spirit of liberal culture in engineering colleges An honor society is an association of primarily collegiate members and chapters whose purposes are to encourage and recognize superior scholarship and or leadership achievement either in broad fields of education or in departmental fields at either undergraduate or graduate levels The honor society has followed the expansion and specialization of higher education in America  When Phi Beta Kappa was organized in       a choice had to be made  and Phi Beta Kappa elected to operate in the field of the liberal arts and sciences  Although this was not finally voted until       the trend was evident years earlier  and      saw the establishment of Tau Beta Pi Founder Edward H  Williams  Jr  was born at Proctorsville  Vermont  on September           he died at Woodstock  Vermont  on November          A member of Phi Beta Kappa  he was head of the mining department at Lehigh University when he determined to offer technical men as good a chance of recognition for superior scholarship in their field as that afforded by Phi Beta Kappa in the liberal arts and sciences Working alone  he conceived an organization  gave it a name  designed its governmental structure  drew up its constitution  prepared its badge and certificate  establish its membership requirements  and planned al the necessary details for its operation including the granting of chapters and the holding of conventions Thus  with only a paper organization  he offered membership to qualified graduates of Lehigh and received their acceptances and enthusiastic endorsement  Late in the spring of       he invited the valedictorian of the senior class  Irving Andrew Heikes  to membership and he accepted  becoming the first student member of Tau Beta Pi  but their was no time to initiate the rest of the eligible men from the class of      Mr  Heikes returned for graduate work  however  and in the fall of       he  Dr  Williams  and two alumni who had earlier accepted membership  initiated the eligible men from the class of      and organized the chapter  The parent chapter  Alpha of Pennsylvania  existed alone until      when Alpha of Michigan was founded at Michigan State University A detailed account of the founding and early history of Tau Beta Pi was written by Edwin S  Stackhouse  after years of painstaking research work  The Bent  April       Records of essential dates were lost  but Mr  Stackhouse deduced that June           was the day on which the first undergraduate student was initiated  Subsequent evidence  in the form of Mr  discovered in       confirmed this date Since the founding of the Michigan Alpha chapter  Tau Beta Pi has grown steadily  there are now collegiate chapters at     institutions  chartered alumnus chapters in    cities  and a total initiated membership of         Login Log in Entries RSS Comments RSS WordPress org  Illinois Zeta Press Customizr 